app.use(cors({ origin: ['https://your-frontend.example'], credentials: true }));
```

### 5. [Low] Hardcoded port, no HTTPS, no graceful shutdown
`app.listen(3000, ...)` assumes the port is unused and binds on all interfaces. In containerized deployments you typically want `process.env.PORT`, and TLS should be terminated at a proxy you trust.

**Fix:**
